468
00:34:04,160 --> 00:34:06,440
أنا لا أعرف حتى
ما هو هذا الشعور... [[ن]] لكني معجب بك يا أرنولد. [[ن]]

469
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:16,559
Now, let's talk about Miss Ran's son.

470
00:34:16,560 --> 00:34:19,840
I heard he showed potential as an actor
since he was young. Is that true, Miss Ran?

471
00:34:20,280 --> 00:34:23,519
Little Raf has always
been confident in front of people.

472
00:34:23,520 --> 00:34:29,599
I had him take acting, singing,
and music classes when he was little.

473
00:34:29,600 --> 00:34:32,399
Wow, he's very skillful.

474
00:34:32,400 --> 00:34:33,479
What about you, Little Raf?

475
00:34:33,480 --> 00:34:35,919
Are you planning to
follow in your mom's footsteps

476
00:34:35,920 --> 00:34:37,600
and enter the entertainment industry?

477
00:34:42,960 --> 00:34:44,960
Uh, I am.

478
00:34:45,280 --> 00:34:50,359
If any producers are watching this,
feel free to contact me directly.

479
00:34:50,360 --> 00:34:52,759
Wow. You're his manager too, yes?

480
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:57,359
He's a handsome young man, and
the son of Miss Ran, a top-tier actress.

481
00:34:57,360 --> 00:35:02,760
I'm sure we can look forward to
a new rising star in the industry.

482
00:35:04,640 --> 00:35:09,920
Lastly, Miss Ran, could you tell the audience
what projects they'll be seeing you in?

483
00:35:10,560 --> 00:35:12,279
I have a TV drama coming out
at the end of the year.

484
00:35:12,280 --> 00:35:17,959
But I'd also like to share that Little Raf
will be starring in his faculty play.

485
00:35:17,960 --> 00:35:20,399
He plays the lead role,
so please stay tuned for that.

486
00:35:20,400 --> 00:35:23,519
Wow, like mother, like son.

487
00:35:23,520 --> 00:35:29,039
Thank you so much today, Miss Ranchalee
and Little Raffy, for speaking with us.

488
00:35:29,040 --> 00:35:30,800
Until next time. Goodbye.

489
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:32,600
Cut.

490
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:34,879
Miss Ran, thank you so much again.

491
00:35:34,880 --> 00:35:36,999
It's truly my pleasure. Thank you so much.

492
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:38,640
Can we get a photo, please?

493
00:35:39,040 --> 00:35:40,040
Of course.

494
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:43,039
I've always been your fan.

495
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:43,920
Thank you so much.

496
00:35:43,921 --> 00:35:45,880
And thank you for interviewing us.

497
00:35:47,840 --> 00:35:48,840
Looking good.

498
00:35:49,480 --> 00:35:50,200
Do you want a picture too?

499
00:35:50,320 --> 00:35:52,640
Come on, step in.

500
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:54,000
She's your fan too.

501
00:35:55,200 --> 00:35:56,560
I dressed up for this.

502
00:35:57,240 --> 00:35:58,720
One, two, three.

503
00:36:00,280 --> 00:36:01,720
One, two, three.

504
00:36:02,640 --> 00:36:03,760
One, two.

505
00:36:03,960 --> 00:36:04,960
Okay.

506
00:36:11,040 --> 00:36:12,040
Raffy.

507
00:36:12,400 --> 00:36:15,560
Next time, if you don't
want to come, just tell her.

508
00:36:17,720 --> 00:36:18,800
I have to.

509
00:36:19,440 --> 00:36:20,560
It's a family show.

510
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:23,200
Are you trying to dig something up?

511
00:36:23,800 --> 00:36:25,160
I'm not digging up anything.

512
00:36:26,240 --> 00:36:27,240
But…

513
00:36:29,350 --> 00:36:30,785
You do like to brag.

514
00:36:31,240 --> 00:36:33,320
You told your mom
you got the lead role in the play.

515
00:36:38,120 --> 00:36:39,120
I didn't tell her.

516
00:36:39,740 --> 00:36:41,260
She just filled in the blanks herself.

517
00:36:46,193 --> 00:36:48,113
I never told my mom I had the lead.

518
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:51,639
I know I'm just a supporting character.

519
00:36:51,640 --> 00:36:55,360
Hey, I didn't mean it like that.

520
00:36:55,800 --> 00:36:57,280
And I'm not blaming you for anything.

521
00:36:58,240 --> 00:36:59,400
I'm just telling the truth.

522
00:37:00,840 --> 00:37:02,040
I only got a supporting role.

523
00:37:02,680 --> 00:37:04,960
And no matter what I do,
my mom will never be proud of me.

524
00:37:06,840 --> 00:37:09,240
That's why I didn't want to come.

525
00:37:16,960 --> 00:37:19,640
Then next time, just tell her
you don't want to come.

526
00:37:19,840 --> 00:37:20,840
What's she gonna do?

527
00:37:31,840 --> 00:37:34,440
Hey, trust me.

528
00:37:35,360 --> 00:37:37,560
I've pulled every kind of
stubborn stunt with my family.

529
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:41,280
If you insist on saying no,
what can anyone do to you?

530
00:37:50,120 --> 00:37:52,239
Come on. Clean off
your makeup and change.

531
00:37:52,240 --> 00:37:53,360
I'll take you back.

532
00:38:02,800 --> 00:38:04,719
Come on, guys. Let's cheers!

533
00:38:04,720 --> 00:38:06,280
- Come on, guys. Let's cheers!
- Cheers!

534
00:38:10,320 --> 00:38:11,440
Listen.

535
00:38:12,480 --> 00:38:17,480
Our backdrop isn't empty anymore
because we've got a sponsor!

536
00:38:19,120 --> 00:38:20,999
Nice work, Timmy.

537
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:23,640
But the money you got
only covers the stage set.

538
00:38:23,760 --> 00:38:25,240
It doesn't include the costumes yet.

539
00:38:25,560 --> 00:38:26,560
What?

540
00:38:26,960 --> 00:38:29,120
It's just the first step, dude.

541
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:32,160
We should be happy
with the small wins first.

542
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:35,200
I'll pitch more sponsors later.

543
00:38:35,560 --> 00:38:38,120
I'm not letting our
actors go on stage naked.

544
00:38:39,120 --> 00:38:41,920
As for you, Jack. Don't be stubborn.

545
00:38:42,800 --> 00:38:44,840
We have to show the sponsor's logo.

546
00:38:45,160 --> 00:38:48,800
The size is exactly
what they asked for. Okay?

547
00:38:49,360 --> 00:38:50,360
Okay.

548
00:38:52,097 --> 00:38:53,720
Ooh! Put it here.

549
00:38:54,280 --> 00:38:57,120
Bring us another bottle of whiskey.
Tell Pink to put it on Jack's tab.

550
00:38:57,280 --> 00:38:59,160
Tonight, it's Jack's treat.

551
00:38:59,320 --> 00:39:00,320
Cheers!

552
00:39:01,880 --> 00:39:03,480
Look how happy you are.

553
00:39:03,920 --> 00:39:07,199
I think the 50K we got today
is going straight into tonight's drinks.

554
00:39:07,200 --> 00:39:08,360
Tua won't get a share.

555
00:39:09,160 --> 00:39:10,160
Of course, he will.

556
00:39:10,161 --> 00:39:11,200
Right, Tua?

557
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:17,880
Tua.

558
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:20,400
Tua.

559
00:39:20,520 --> 00:39:21,520
Hey.

560
00:39:24,080 --> 00:39:25,080
Is something wrong?

561
00:39:26,360 --> 00:39:27,040
Nothing.

562
00:39:27,041 --> 00:39:28,640
Then let's cheers.

563
00:39:32,720 --> 00:39:34,120
Just let me know if something's up.

564
00:39:36,360 --> 00:39:37,960
I'm gonana use the bathroom.

565
00:39:38,640 --> 00:39:39,280
Don't take too long.
Yeah.

566
00:39:44,240 --> 00:39:45,240
Here.

567
00:39:53,680 --> 00:39:55,240
Do you model often?

568
00:39:56,240 --> 00:39:57,240
This is my first time.

569
00:39:57,920 --> 00:39:59,600
I've always wondered what it's like.

570
00:40:00,720 --> 00:40:03,880
If you're ready, take off your shirt.
I'll set up the camera.

571
00:40:42,800 --> 00:40:43,800
How should I pose?

572
00:40:47,560 --> 00:40:50,240
However you like.
Any pose you feel comfortable with.

573
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:57,800
We'll start now.

574
00:41:24,760 --> 00:41:29,360
If I grab your ass once,
how much will that cost, James Dean?

575
00:41:30,960 --> 00:41:33,840
If you're so desperate to grab an ass,
why don't you try your dad's?

576
00:41:34,840 --> 00:41:35,960
Whoa, you prick.

577
00:41:39,880 --> 00:41:40,920
Aren't you a hooker?

578
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:42,000
I'm not.

579
00:41:42,160 --> 00:41:43,280
I'm just a host.

580
00:41:43,720 --> 00:41:47,520
And if I were selling myself, I wouldn't
sell it to some ugly asshole like you.

581
00:41:48,120 --> 00:41:49,120
Mouthy, aren't you?

582
00:41:55,880 --> 00:41:58,080
Ugly face and an ugly personality too,
you motherfucker!

583
00:41:59,320 --> 00:42:00,320
Let go of me!

584
00:42:01,200 --> 00:42:02,376
What the hell are you guys doing?

585
00:42:02,400 --> 00:42:03,400
Son of a bitch!

586
00:42:06,920 --> 00:42:09,280
I was negotiating with a host.
Why the fuck did you butt in?

587
00:42:09,400 --> 00:42:10,400
So you're not gonna stop?

588
00:42:10,600 --> 00:42:11,600
Got a problem?

589
00:42:11,640 --> 00:42:12,200
Just go.
Let's leave.

590
00:42:38,240 --> 00:42:39,240
Hey.

591
00:42:39,760 --> 00:42:42,240
Aren't Jack and Dean
coming back to the table?

592
00:42:43,160 --> 00:42:44,680
I gotta go. There's an emergency.

593
00:42:45,120 --> 00:42:46,120
What?!

594
00:42:46,760 --> 00:42:48,200
You're leaving too?

595
00:42:48,960 --> 00:42:49,960
Tua!

596
00:42:51,960 --> 00:42:53,160
Fine, I'll drink alone.

597
00:42:58,040 --> 00:42:59,960
Ouch. Jack, that hurts.

598
00:43:01,920 --> 00:43:04,720
I see you don't like
being the lead in a romantic play.

599
00:43:04,960 --> 00:43:06,640
You'd rather be the lead in an action one.

600
00:43:09,040 --> 00:43:12,040
Thanks a lot anyway.

601
00:43:12,600 --> 00:43:17,120
Without you, I'd have been
outnumbered and beaten up.

602
00:43:21,200 --> 00:43:22,680
I won't let anything happen to you.

603
00:43:23,840 --> 00:43:26,040
Besides, those guys were real assholes.

604
00:43:27,000 --> 00:43:28,000
True.

605
00:43:29,560 --> 00:43:34,120
If someone like me is going to get groped,
I should at least get paid for it.

606
00:43:36,440 --> 00:43:37,959
You've still got the nerve
to joke about it, huh?

607
00:43:37,960 --> 00:43:40,160
Ouch, Jack. It hurts.

608
00:43:50,320 --> 00:43:51,360
What can I do?

609
00:43:52,120 --> 00:43:53,520
I can't change my past.

610
00:43:54,960 --> 00:43:57,640
All I can do is decide how to deal with it.

611
00:43:59,640 --> 00:44:00,976
From now on, I'm not going to be afraid.

612
00:44:01,000 --> 00:44:04,520
If someone tries to pick a fight,
I'll freaking fight back.

613
00:44:26,040 --> 00:44:29,680
When I said I wanted to change,

614
00:44:34,120 --> 00:44:35,360
I meant it.

615
00:44:38,200 --> 00:44:39,560
I want to be the new Dean for you.

616
00:44:48,560 --> 00:44:49,560
Do you still love me?

617
00:45:01,280 --> 00:45:02,840
I don't want to throw that word around.

618
00:45:05,680 --> 00:45:07,000
But I really want to hear…

619
00:45:10,200 --> 00:45:11,480
if you still love me or not.

620
00:45:33,320 --> 00:45:34,320
You got your answer?

621
00:45:35,840 --> 00:45:36,840
Mm.

622
00:45:57,640 --> 00:45:59,120
How long have you and Tua been close?

623
00:46:00,080 --> 00:46:00,800
Quite long.

624
00:46:01,000 --> 00:46:02,000
Since our first year.

625
00:46:03,240 --> 00:46:04,840
You two don't look like you're friends.

626
00:46:06,160 --> 00:46:07,200
Looks like something else.

627
00:46:13,480 --> 00:46:17,680
Actually, I came to see you today
because I wanted to talk about that.

628
00:46:21,280 --> 00:46:22,600
Stop making Tua uncomfortable.

629
00:46:23,680 --> 00:46:24,760
Tua doesn't like you.

630
00:46:28,440 --> 00:46:29,440
Why?

631
00:46:30,280 --> 00:46:31,280
Do you like him?

632
00:46:35,920 --> 00:46:36,920
I'm not sure.

633
00:46:39,120 --> 00:46:40,520
That's not a good enough answer.

634
00:46:41,383 --> 00:46:43,053
If you're not sure, you'd better back off.

635
00:46:44,059 --> 00:46:47,419
I feel good about him,
and I care about him a lot.

636
00:46:48,666 --> 00:46:50,386
Even if I'm not sure about my feelings yet,

637
00:46:51,640 --> 00:46:57,280
I'm sure someone like Tua
is too good for you.

638
00:46:59,040 --> 00:47:02,520
And how are you so sure
Tua doesn't have feelings for me?

639
00:47:09,880 --> 00:47:13,880
And if I leave him alone,
what do I get out of it?

640
00:47:19,440 --> 00:47:21,600
If you've got something better to offer me…

641
00:47:26,600 --> 00:47:27,760
I might change my mind.

642
00:47:34,800 --> 00:47:35,800
What are you two doing?

643
00:47:37,920 --> 00:47:39,960
Whoa. You really came all this way?

644
00:47:40,840 --> 00:47:43,080
Are you afraid I might
do something to your close friend?

645
00:47:46,720 --> 00:47:47,720
And what are you doing?

646
00:47:50,080 --> 00:47:53,480
I'm not doing anything. We're just talking.

647
00:47:53,680 --> 00:47:54,680
Right?

648
00:47:56,800 --> 00:47:58,000
Arnold's worried about you.

649
00:47:58,320 --> 00:47:59,680
He wants me to stay away from you.

650
00:48:01,080 --> 00:48:03,280
What did you say just now, Arnold?

651
00:48:03,699 --> 00:48:04,979
How do you feel about Tua again?

652
00:48:10,000 --> 00:48:11,000
I…

653
00:48:13,713 --> 00:48:15,313
What exactly were you two talking about?

654
00:48:15,800 --> 00:48:16,800
About me?

655
00:48:24,920 --> 00:48:26,440
Well, you've had my attention lately.

656
00:48:27,680 --> 00:48:29,040
Who else would I be talking about?

657
00:49:04,320 --> 00:49:05,560
Leave Tua alone.

658
00:49:21,760 --> 00:49:23,839
(Next Episode)
Timmy and I spoke with the sponsor.

659
00:49:23,840 --> 00:49:25,759
They wanted leads with a large following.

660
00:49:25,784 --> 00:49:28,309
So they suggested Raffy
take the lead role too.

661
00:49:28,334 --> 00:49:29,969
Even though we
had a fair casting…

662
00:49:30,000 --> 00:49:32,235
Why are you stealing
the lead role from me?

663
00:49:32,260 --> 00:49:32,739
What the hell are you talking about?

664
00:49:32,764 --> 00:49:33,879
Are you playing dumb?

665
00:49:33,904 --> 00:49:34,728
Why were you drinking alone?
I was bored…

666
00:49:35,794 --> 00:49:36,574
needed something to kill time.

667
00:49:36,841 --> 00:49:37,914
I can accompany you.

668
00:49:39,864 --> 00:49:41,577
I don't really have an answer.

669
00:49:41,602 --> 00:49:43,234
I don't even know
what this feeling is…

670
00:49:43,259 --> 00:49:44,507
But I like you, Arnold.

